snippet: More than six months after protesters drove Viktor F. Yanukovych from power, his lavish estate displays how difficult it is to bring about a real break with Ukraine’s past.
abstract: Former Ukrainian President Viktor F Yanukovych's lavish estate near Kiev is symbol of how difficult it is to bring about real change in troubled nation; $1 billion property, which has not yet been taken over by state despite him being driven from power over six months ago, stands as warning that Ukraine's troubles reach far beyond war zone in east of country.
lead_paragraph: More than six months after protesters drove Viktor F. Yanukovych from power, his lavish estate displays how difficult it is to bring about a real break with Ukraine’s past.

headline.main: Ukraine Palace Is Still Emblem of Dysfunction
headline.print_headline: Ukraine Palace Is Still Emblem of Dysfunction
